  "instructions": [
    "Toast the cornflakes in a dry skillet over medium heat until golden and fragrant, about 2 minutes. Remove and let cool.",
    "Whisk coconut milk, fish sauce, calamansi juice, white sugar, toasted garlic powder, sesame oil, salt, and black pepper in a small bowl until the sugar dissolves.",
    "Gently toss the diced avocado with the dressing, ensuring all pieces are coated.",
    "Sprinkle the toasted cornflakes over the avocado mixture for a crunchy texture.",
    "Top with chopped fresh cilantro, if using.",
    "Serve immediately or chill in the refrigerator for 15 minutes to allow flavors to meld.",
    "Enjoy as a light snack or side salad."
  ],
